properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 2 at 2:01PM MST until January 4 at 11:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...STRONG WINDS RETURNING TO SOUTHEAST WYOMING FRIDAY INTO THE
WEEKEND...

The National Weather Service in Cheyenne has issued a High Wind
Watch, which is in effect from Saturday morning through Saturday
evening.

* WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 65 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Western portions of the Laramie Valley to include Quealy
Dome and Rock River.

* WHEN...From Saturday afternoon through Saturday evening.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Travel could be hazardous
for light weight and high profile vehicles, including camping
and tractor trailers. There could be an elevated blow over risk
along Interstate 80 near Quealy Dome and Rock River.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY MORNING THROUGH SATURDAY EVENING
